    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review effectiveness of post separation domestic abuse laws",
        "additional_details": "The Government are the only people who can introduce this law. We believe that too many people are left suffering in a flawed system that abusers use to maintain control and keep the abuse going long after the relationship ends.",
        "background": "We want the  Government to review the effectiveness of existing laws on post-separation domestic abuse and Introduce further provisions that will deter abusers from using loopholes in the legal system to continue abuse.",
